July 14, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Babcock & Wilcox Enterprises, I shares had a trading volume of 1,176K on Friday.  Volume was up 293.64% over the stocks average daily volume. 
 These funds have also shifted positions in (BW).   As of quarter end Howe & Rusling Inc had disposed of 16 shares trimming its stake by 8.6%. The value of the total investment in Babcock & Wilcox Enterprises, I went from $2,000 to $2,000 a change of 0.0% for the reporting period. As of the end of the quarter Creative Planning had sold  a total of 54 shares trimming its position 14.1%. The value of the company’s investment in Babcock & Wilcox Enterprises, I decreased from $4,000 to $4,000 a change of $0 quarter over quarter.
 As of quarter end Bank Of Montreal /can/ had disposed of  a total of 5,412 shares trimming its holdings by 79.3%. The value of the investment in (BW) went from $64,000 to $17,000 decreasing 73.4% since the last quarter. Symphony Asset Management LLC trimmed its stake by selling 26,602 shares a decrease of 35.2% as of 12/31/2016. Symphony Asset Management LLC controls 48,915 shares valued at $811,000. The value of the position overall is down by 34.9%.
  On October 13 the company was downgraded to “Underperform” from “Neutral” by analysts at Credit Suisse. February 29 investment analysts at Credit Suisse maintained a stock rating of “Neutral” and moved up the price target  to $21.00 from $20.00.        Advertisement






 Equity analyst BB&T Capital initiated coverage on the stock with an initial rating of “Buy” and a price target of $24.00. On July 8 analysts at Johnson Rice started covering the stock giving it an initial rating of “Buy” and price target of $26.00.
 UBS issued its first research report on the stock by announcing an initial rating of “Buy” and setting a price target of $25.00.
 The company is up by 0.86 percent from yesterday’s close.  It is trading at $10.58 a tad under $11.02, the 50 day moving average and marginally under the 200 day moving average of $12.64.  The 50 day moving average went down $-0.44 or -3.98% whereas the 200 day average was down by -16.32%. 
 In the last earnings report the EPS was $-2.70 and is projected to be $0.77 for the current year with 48,831,000 shares currently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS to be $0.32 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $1.00. 
 Babcock & Wilcox Enterprises, Inc., launched on January 13, 2015, is a technology-based provider of fossil and renewable power generation and environmental equipment that includes a suite of boiler products and environmental systems, and services for power and industrial uses. The Company operates in three segments: Power, Renewable and Industrial. The Company specializes in technology and engineering for power generation and various other industries, the related procurement, erection and specialty manufacturing of equipment. The Company is also engaged in the provision of related services, including high-pressure equipment for energy conversion, such as boilers fueled by coal, oil, bitumen, natural gas and renewables, including municipal solid waste and biomass fuels; environmental control systems for both power generation and industrial applications to incinerate, filter, capture, recover and/or purify air, liquid and vapor-phase effluents from a range of power generation and specialty manufacturing processes; aftermarket support for the global installed base of operating plants with a range of products and technical services, including replacement parts, retrofit and upgrade capabilities, field engineering, construction, inspection, operations and maintenance, condition assessment and other technical support; gas turbine inlet and exhaust systems, custom silencers, filters and custom enclosures, and engineered-to-order services, products and systems for energy conversion around the world and related auxiliary equipment, such as burners, pulverizers, soot blowers, and ash and material handling systems..
